@startuml
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #E8F4F8
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActorBackgroundColor #FFE6CC

title SD-07 - Password Reset Flow

actor Administrator
participant Browser
participant Server
participant Router
participant Controller
participant Model
database Database
participant Email

Administrator -> Browser: 1. Navigate to forgot password\nGET /administrator/lupapassword
activate Browser

Browser -> Server: 2. GET /administrator/lupapassword
activate Server
deactivate Browser

Server -> Router: 3. Route to Administrator controller lupapassword()
activate Router
deactivate Server

Router -> Controller: 4. Call lupapassword() method
activate Controller
deactivate Router

note right of Controller
    Setup forgot password form:
    - Generate captcha
    - Load forgot password template
end note

Controller -> Browser: 5. Render forgot password template\n(template().'/administrator/lupapassword', $data)
activate Browser

Browser -> Administrator: 6. Display forgot password form\nwith captcha
deactivate Browser

Administrator -> Browser: 7. Enter email and submit\nPOST /administrator/lupapassword
activate Browser

Browser -> Server: 8. POST /administrator/lupapassword\n(email, captcha)
activate Server
deactivate Browser

Server -> Router: 9. Route to Administrator controller lupapassword() (POST)
activate Router
deactivate Server

Router -> Controller: 10. Call lupapassword() method (POST)
activate Controller
deactivate Router

note right of Controller
    Validate form submission:
    - Check required fields
    - Verify captcha
    - Check if email exists in users table
end note

Controller -> Model: 11. view_where('users',['email'=>$email])
activate Model

Model -> Database: 12. SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE email = '$email'
activate Database
deactivate Model

Database --> Model: 13. Return user data or empty
deactivate Database
activate Model

Model --> Controller: 14. Return user data
deactivate Model
activate Controller

alt Email exists
    note right of Controller
        Generate reset token:
        - Create random token
        - Store token in database
        - Send email with reset link
    end note

    Controller -> Model: 15. update('users', ['reset_token'=>$token, 'reset_expiry'=>$expiry], ['email'=>$email])
    activate Model

    Model -> Database: 16. UPDATE users SET reset_token = '$token',\nreset_expiry = '$expiry' WHERE email = '$email'
    activate Database
    deactivate Model

    Database --> Model: 17. Update successful
    deactivate Database
    activate Model

    Model --> Controller: 18. Return update result
    deactivate Model
    activate Controller

    note right of Controller
        Send reset email:
        - Configure email settings
        - Send HTML email with reset link
    end note

    Controller -> Email: 19. Send reset email\nto user email
    activate Email

    Email -> Email: 20. Send email via SMTP
    note right of Email
        Email contains:
        - Reset link: /administrator/reset_password/$token
        - Expiration notice
    end note

    Email --> Controller: 21. Email sent successfully
    deactivate Email
    activate Controller

    Controller -> Browser: 22. Render success message\ntemplate
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Administrator: 23. Display success message\n"Check your email"
    deactivate Browser

else Email not found
    Controller -> Browser: 24. Render error message\ntemplate
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Administrator: 25. Display error message\n"Email not found"
    deactivate Browser
end

opt User clicks reset link
    Administrator -> Browser: 26. Click reset link from email\nGET /administrator/reset_password/token
    activate Browser

    Browser -> Server: 27. GET /administrator/reset_password/token
    activate Server
    deactivate Browser

    Server -> Router: 28. Route to Administrator controller reset_password()
    activate Router
    deactivate Server

    Router -> Controller: 29. Call reset_password() method
    activate Controller
    deactivate Router

    note right of Controller
        Validate reset token:
        - Check if token exists
        - Verify token not expired
        - Load reset password form
    end note

    Controller -> Model: 30. view_where('users',['reset_token'=>$token])
    activate Model

    Model -> Database: 31. SELECT * FROM users\nWHERE reset_token = '$token'
    activate Database
    deactivate Model

    Database --> Model: 32. Return user data
    deactivate Database
    activate Model

    Model --> Controller: 33. Return user data
    deactivate Model
    activate Controller

    alt Token valid and not expired
        Controller -> Browser: 34. Render reset password form\n(template().'/administrator/reset_password', $data)
        activate Browser

        Browser -> Administrator: 35. Display reset password form
        deactivate Browser

        Administrator -> Browser: 36. Enter new password and submit\nPOST /administrator/reset_password/token
        activate Browser

        Browser -> Server: 37. POST /administrator/reset_password/token\n(new_password, confirm_password)
        activate Server
        deactivate Browser

        Server -> Router: 38. Route to Administrator controller reset_password() (POST)
        activate Router
        deactivate Server

        Router -> Controller: 39. Call reset_password() method (POST)
        activate Controller
        deactivate Router

        note right of Controller
            Update password:
            - Hash new password with MD5
            - Clear reset token
            - Redirect to login
        end note

        Controller -> Model: 40. update('users', ['password'=>md5($new_password), 'reset_token'=>'', 'reset_expiry'=>''], ['reset_token'=>$token])
        activate Model

        Model -> Database: 41. UPDATE users SET password = MD5('$new_password'),\nreset_token = '', reset_expiry = ''\nWHERE reset_token = '$token'
        activate Database
        deactivate Model

        Database --> Model: 42. Update successful
        deactivate Database
        activate Model

        Model --> Controller: 43. Return update result
        deactivate Model
        activate Controller

        Controller -> Browser: 44. redirect('administrator')
        activate Browser

        Browser -> Administrator: 45. Redirect to login page\nwith success message
        deactivate Browser

    else Token invalid or expired
        Controller -> Browser: 46. Render error message\ntemplate
        activate Browser

        Browser -> Administrator: 47. Display error message\n"Invalid or expired link"
        deactivate Browser
    end
end

@enduml
